An athletic, girlish ch\@taren, Alhaia Ki\@Lymir stands as if she were a
dozen feet tall.  With narrow shoulders and a small frame, her actual size
is anything but intimidating.  The grip of time, it seems, holds no sway
over the Twin-Daughter, giving her the lively look and manner of perpetual
youth.  

Long, sterling curls cascade across her narrow shoulders, nine white roses
woven into their fall.  Her eyes are a vivid plum, made all the more
striking by her shimmering, timeless face.  A braided silver chain rests at
he base of her slender neck, while a pair of amethyst earrings dangle from
one of her ears.  Along her right arm, a series of small, glittering dots
twist up from the elbow, surrounding a tear-shaped mark.  Below her left
shoulder, a shining Pegasus brand emits its own divine light.  

During the Eyeblight War, she acted as a lieutenant of the Surface Alliance
and leader of the liberators of the Spirit Palace.  Having garnered the
favor of Rystaia, she was branded as a Chosen at the age of fourteen.  She
would later be accepted by the Vaialan Zseania Saxeitu, and ultimately
anointed as a Knight of Aramril.  Known as the Champion of Light, she held
the ranks of both Paladin and Lady General during her tenure.  She now
dwells within the Shrine of Rystaia, basking in the joy of the Lady in whose
name she lived.  
