A small, angular annex onto the temple proper, the portal chamber is much
like the faceted surface of a cut jewel from the inside.  The floor cuts
downward, then upward again, while the walls of this place shift unevenly
and at abrupt edges.  Much like the rest of the temple, the chamber seems to
be constructed from increasingly more transparent marble.  The enshrouding
mist of the temple is visible through the gemstone barriers, each a slightly
different shade in color.  Three of the larger facets are particularly
colorful and luminous, images flickering within them of different places. 
To the east, the silvery floor leads back into the temple.  
